  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Assisting the Government of Ghana to Combat Child Trafficking</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to establish a more holistic approach to significantly reduce child trafficking (child sex trafficking and child labor) in Ghana, especially in Greater Accra, Central and Volta Regions. It is expected that an improved coordination of activities, enhanced efforts to prevent trafficking, to prosecute and convict child traffickers, and to improve the quality of protection and direct assistance services for child victims will create a critical positive shift in the current state of affairs. This is in line with the Child Protection Compact recently signed between the U.S. Government and the Government of Ghana.</narrative>
  </description>
